# UI Theme Overhaul: Light Mode Default

I have successfully transitioned the application to a **Light Mode default** theme with a premium, high-contrast aesthetic. This was achieved by systematically replacing hardcoded color classes with semantic theme variables across the entire codebase.

## Key Accomplishments

### 🎨 Semantic Theme Integration
- **[globals.css](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/globals.css)**: Defined a robust set of semantic color tokens (background, foreground, card, secondary, muted, border, etc.) for both light and dark modes.
- **[layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/layout.tsx)**: Configured the application to default to the light theme by adding the `light` class to the `html` tag and setting `colorScheme: 'light'`.

### 📱 Component Refactoring
All major feature views and components have been updated to be fully theme-aware:

