## Visual Improvements
- **Typography**: Extensive use of `font-black` and `font-mono` for headers and identifiers to create a strong visual hierarchy.
- **Micro-animations**: Added subtle transition effects, hover scales, and spin animations for a more responsive feel.
- **Shadows & Borders**: Used `shadow-sm`, `shadow-xl`, and `border-border/50` to create depth and separate content areas effectively.

## Final Result
The application now presents a cohesive, professional, and accessible interface that feels significantly more premium. While light mode is the new standard, the system remains fully compatible with dark mode fallback.

> [!TIP]
> You can verify the new theme by navigating through the various views (Next Sprint, Daily Meeting, etc.). All elements should now respect the light mode variables while maintaining high legibility.

## Final Verification

The UI overhaul has been verified across all major modules using Chrome. The application now defaults to a premium light mode with high-contrast elements, regardless of system preferences.

